name: podamShouldHandleConstructorsWithMultipleGenericsDuringPojoInstantiation

testSteps.description: When I invoke the factory manufacturing for class uk.co.jemos.podam.test.dto.MultipleGenericInConstructorPojo with specific types {class java.lang.String,class java.lang.Character,class java.lang.Byte,class java.lang.Integer}
Then the pojo uk.co.jemos.podam.test.dto.MultipleGenericInConstructorPojo@19406d0 must be of the type class uk.co.jemos.podam.test.dto.MultipleGenericInConstructorPojo
Then the two objects class java.lang.String and class java.lang.String should be equal
Then the collection should not be null or empty and each element should be of type class java.lang.Character
Then the Map should not be null or empty and each element should have key of type class java.lang.Byte and value of type class java.lang.Integer

title: Podam should handle constructors with multiple generics during Pojo instantiation
